Chose the Pick2 half sandwich/half soup - Chicken Pomodori and Tortilla Soup - Soup was good, can't really mess that up - Sandwich was a mess. I come here fairly often since it's close to where I work. The food isn't bad for the price, but the service is absolutely awful. Even if no one is ahead of me in line, I often have to wait 20 or 30 minutes to get served. That's right, a half hour wait for a sandwich!  It's probably because the staff is never on task. While they leave the cash registers and kitchen unmanned, you can see them chatting and taking breaks even during high traffic hours. If you value your time, it's probably best to try any of the other similar cafes around the loop.
